    <title>SAP Build Apps Integration of a Process Error 500</title>
    <updated>2024-12-12T12:00:22.175000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>HSam</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/1905753</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;I wanted to send a short E-Mail with the status of an object from my app and was trying to use a process from Process Automation for that.&lt;BR /&gt;To learn how to do that, I tried following these tutorials:&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;A href="https://developers.sap.com/tutorials/codejam-07-connect-app-process..html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://developers.sap.com/tutorials/codejam-07-connect-app-process..html&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;A href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8RVo3-h2n-I" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8RVo3-h2n-I&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I created a Service Key and a Destination as it was described in the tutorials with the name "sap_process_automation_service_user_access" and set URL, Client ID, Client Secret and Token Service URL the way the tutorial said.&lt;BR /&gt;URL: API from Service key&lt;BR /&gt;Client ID and Client Secret: Client ID and Client Secret from Service Key&lt;BR /&gt;Token Service URL: URL/oauth/token&lt;BR /&gt;When I press Check Connection it says that the Connection is established (Response: 401).&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The Process was also released, deployed and published to Library and it is being displayed in the Integrations Tab of my App in "SAP Build Library.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="HSam_0-1734000015403.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/200969iCBA62604159F1A26/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="HSam_0-1734000015403.png" alt="HSam_0-1734000015403.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;However, if I then click on any of the Processes it loads for a while and then says "something went wrong"&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="HSam_1-1734000079082.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/200972iB88A1001E3EFAABB/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="HSam_1-1734000079082.png" alt="HSam_1-1734000079082.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;And in the console it throws 3 Response Errors with the Status Code 500&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="HSam_2-1734000165567.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/200974i3DABDB00C67180AF/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="HSam_2-1734000165567.png" alt="HSam_2-1734000165567.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="HSam_3-1734000178172.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/200975i989CB1CD5A52F228/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="HSam_3-1734000178172.png" alt="HSam_3-1734000178172.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I have tried this on different days, in different browsers and on different systems. I set up the Subscriptions from the ground up and tried it again, I deleted and recreated the destination and service keys multiple times, but nothing of that has helped.&lt;BR /&gt;I also thought that maybe it was because the Destinations tab in the Control Tower was empty and added my destination in there as well and I have tried to use the sample process and App provided by the Youtube Tutorial, but even then the same error occured.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/sap-build-apps-integration-of-a-process-error-500/qaq-p/13961940"/>
    <published>2024-12-12T12:00:22.175000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
